title: Colombia Gaitania (Espresso)
description: Region: Tolima Varietal: Caturra, Typica Processing: Fully Washed Altitude: 1700 - 2000 MASL Tastes Like: Caramelized Peach, Vanilla, Hazelnut This is our second permanent espresso offering! It features soft brown sugar notes balanced with a light stone fruit sweetness that shows up well in an espresso and in a black coffee. Bulk Purchase available. Contact us!

title: Brazil Sul De Minas Watsatubi (Espresso)
description: Region: Sul De Minas Varietal: Red Catuai Processing: Natural Process Altitude: 1050 - 1,300 MASL Tastes Like: Honey, Caramelized Nuts, Dark Chocolate Our House Roast is available for your enjoyment at home! We call it "The Usual", which is what everyone wants when they make their orders (: Origin for the coffee will change occasionally depending on seasonality and quality. Specially roasted for Espresso and Cold Brew, it is a full-bodied, non acidic, and a comforting cup. Best for your therapeutic afternoons! Available as whole beans and ground (just mention what brewing equipment you are using, and we will grind it for you!) Bulk Purchase available. Contact us!
